SIMPLE: surety
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Surety
<hw>Sure"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sureties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>seurte</ets>, OF.
<ets>se⟦uum⟧rt⟦eacute⟧</ets>, F. <ets>s⟦ucir⟧ret⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Sure</er>, <er>Security</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of
being sure; certainty; security.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Know of a <qex>surety</qex>, that thy seed shall be a stranger in
a land that is not theirs.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xv. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For the more <qex>surety</qex> they looked round about.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which makes sure; that which confirms; ground
of confidence or security.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[We] our happy state⟦br⟧
Hold, as you yours, while our obedience holds;⟦br⟧
On other <qex>surety</qex> none.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Security against loss or damage; security for
payment, or for the performance of some act.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There remains unpaid⟦br⟧
A hundred thousand more; in <qex>surety</qex> of the which⟦br⟧
One part of Aquitaine is bound to us.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who is bound with and for
another who is primarily liable, and who is called the
<xex>principal</xex>; one who engages to answer for another's appearance
in court, or for his payment of a debt, or for performance of some act;
a bondsman; a bail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that is <qex>surety</qex> for a stranger shall smart for
it.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xi. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Hence, a substitute; a hostage.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Evidence; confirmation; warrant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She called the saints to <qex>surety</qex>,⟦br⟧
That she would never put it from her finger,⟦br⟧
Unless she gave it to yourself.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surety</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Surety
<hw>Sure"ty</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To act as surety for.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suretyship</ent>⟦br⟧
